1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Di vê carê jî, di zincîreya gundê me da, em ê berê xwe bidin
gundê Sînka.
 
This time as well, in our series "Our Village", we will head
to the village of Sînka.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Di vê carê em li gundê Sînka ne.
 
This time we are in the village of Sînka.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Ev gundê Sînka girêdayî navçeya Şera ye.
 
This village of Sînka is tied to the district of Shera.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Ev gundê Sînka 300 mal e.
 
This village of Sînka has 300 houses.

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Gundekî kevin e.
 
It is an old village.

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Du gund jî ji vê gundî peyda bûne, wek gundê Qestelê û wek
gundê Baflûnê.
 
Two other villages have emerged from this village, like the
village of Qestel and Baflûn.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Ev gundê Sînka, du ol tê de jiyan dikin. Misilman û Êzidî.
 
This village of Sînka, two religions live in it. Muslims and
Yezidis.

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Lê di vê carê de jî em ê bibin mêvanên gundê Sînka.
 
But this time we will be the guests of the village of Sînka.

9
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Mamoste, merheba, çawa yî?
 
Teacher, hello, how are you?

10
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Wey ehlen we sehlen. Serçavan hatin.
 
Oh, welcome. You came on my eyes (you are very welcome).

11
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Sax bî mamoste.
 
Be healthy, teacher.

12
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Me xwest, em di gundê Sînka da, em destpêkê derbasî cem te
bin.
 
We wanted to, in the village of Sînka, first visit you.

13
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Wey ser serê min, hatina we ser çavê min e.
 
Oh, on my head, your arrival is on my eyes.

14
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Spasdar im jê.
 
I am thankful for it.

15
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Di gund de behsa te kirin, gotin "Mamosteyek li vir heye, ew
jî karê wî wênesaz e."
 
In the village they mentioned you, they said, "There is a
teacher here, and his profession is painting."

16
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Me jî meraq kir em derbasî cem te bin.
 
We were curious to visit you.

17
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Destpêkê navê xwe bêje, û çend sal e tu vî karî dikî?
 
First of all, tell us your name, and how many years have you
been doing this work?

18
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Welleh ez, navê min Mihemed Çawîş e. Ji vir, dibêjin Bavê
Ehmed.
 
By God, my name is Mihemed Çawîş. Around here, they call me
Bavê Ehmed.

19
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Û ji biçûkatiya xwe de, ez ku diçûme mektebê, di sefî yekê
da, min ji resim hez kir.
 
And since my childhood, when I went to school, in the first
grade, I loved drawing.

20
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Yanî ez tiştê rastî bêjim, rojekî bi diya xwe re çûm bazarê,
min ew telwîn dîtin.
 
I mean, to tell the truth, one day I went to the market with
my mother, and I saw those crayons.

21
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Min hez kir wiha, bi deha warqan min kirrî. Min za'f ji
resmê hez dikir.
 
I liked them like that, I bought them for ten bills. I loved
drawing a lot.

22
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Û ma, kir ew karê xwe jî. Û heta roha hîr e, em resim dikin.
 
And it stayed, it became our work. And until today, we draw.

23
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Û hezkirina me ji resim ra, me kir ev û em naxwazin vî tiştî
ji bîr bikin.
 
And our love for drawing made us do this and we don't want
to forget this thing.

24
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Mamoste Mihemed, ev çend sal e tu vî karî dikî? Karê
wênesaz?
 
Teacher Mihemed, how many years have you been doing this
work? The work of painting?

25
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Karê wênesaz, ez karim ji te ra bêjim, ku ez kar, wek kar,
ji sala nod û duda da ez resim dikim.
 
The work of painting, I can tell you that as work, I have
been drawing since '92.

26
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Ketim nav çarşiyê... min destpê kir...
 
I entered the market... I started...

27
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Bû yek karê me... Em di pey re, tiştên gundan... ez çûm
Lubnanê, me'red, me li wê derê wek dibêjin iştirak kir.
 
It became our work... Afterwards, things of the villages...
I went to Lebanon, an exhibition, we participated there as
they say.

28
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Û ew be yanî, alema şixulê me ecibandin. Û her em çûn em pêş
ketin.
 
And well, I mean, the people liked our work. And we kept
advancing.

29
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Û me karê xwe berneda. Em şev û roj di şixulin yanî tiştek
wilo.
 
And we didn't abandon our work. We work day and night,
something like that.

30
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Te li kîderê, cihê te hebû? Navend hebû?
 
Where did you, did you have a place? Did you have a center?

31
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Navenda min li Helebê bû. Li Helebê min navendek bi rê ve
dibir, em di xwe re di şixulîn.
 
My center was in Aleppo. In Aleppo I ran a center, we were
working for ourselves.

32
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:03,000
Û hevalên me jî za'f bûn, dehatin cem me, me ji wan ra digot
ev karê me ye.
 
And our friends were many, they came to us, we told them
this is our work.

33
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:08,000
Û ka kanim bêjim jî, sala nod û sêya min me'hed xwend.
Me'heda resmê li Helebê.
 
And I can also say, in the year ninety-three I studied at an
institute. The painting institute in Aleppo.

34
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Me du salan xwend, bi xêr û selamet. Me çar dewrî qedand,
tiştek wilo.
 
We studied for two years, safely and soundly. We finished
four semesters, something like that.

35
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Mamoste, kanî hinek behsa wêneyên xwe jî bikî?
 
Teacher, can you talk a little about your paintings?

36
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Yanî wênesazên te jî, hemî jî balkêş in, bi rastî yanî,
tiştên gundî ne.
 
I mean, your paintings, they are all interesting, truly,
they are village themes.

37
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Tiştên gundî ne. Kanî ji kerema te di vir da were.
 
They are village themes. Please come here.

38
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Ev, ne ev cotar e. Kî ye ev? Gelo ew cotarê kî bû ev wextî
gundî?
 
This, isn't this a farmer. Who is this? Who was that farmer
back in the village times?

39
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Welleh ez, zanim... ez, min didît ku di gundê me da cotarî
pir bûn.
 
By God, I know... I, I saw that in our village there were a
lot of farmers.

40
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Yanî berê traktor kêm dan dikirin... bi cotê dewar bûn.
 
I mean in the past, tractors were used less... it was plowed
with draft animals.

41
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Ew bêndergêr wilo da bûn... ew cotar ewa... deware...
 
Those threshers were like that... that farmer there...
animals...

42
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Min dît yek hebû navê wî digotin Elî Xelek. Em wer wî
dibûn... Heta hat, di bala min da ma.
 
I saw there was one they called Elî Xelek. We would be
around him... Until it came, it stayed in my mind.

43
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Yanî heya niha, sîfeta wî, xwedê rehma xwe lê bike, di bala
min de bûye.
 
I mean until now, his face, may God have mercy on him, has
been on my mind.

44
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Ez vê sibê rabûme ji eşqê we re. Gotin televîzyona Ronahî wê
were cem te, min tabloyeke wî danî...
 
I woke up this morning out of excitement for you. They said
Ronahî TV will come to you, I set up a painting of him...

45
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Elî Xelek hat bîra min, min ev tablo dîna, min destê xwe
resim kir. Heta hun hatin gihîştin cem min.
 
Elî Xelek came to my mind, I set up this painting, I drew it
with my hand. Until you arrived to me.

46
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Yanî ev karê te yê vê sibê ye?
 
So this is your work from this morning?

47
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Ewa karê min yê vê sibê ye. Erê, ev vê sibê, eva jî cem bî
heval dibê...
 
That is my work from this morning. Yes, this morning, this
also along with the friend...

48
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Ez, gund şiyar nebûne rûniştim... min sîneyê xwe çêkir,
derketim derve resm kir.
 
I, before the village woke up, sat... I prepared my easel, I
went outside and painted.

49
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Bes na wext tine bû bo min, an ku ez tiştekî zêde tê de
bikim. Lê me eva çêkir.
 
But no, I had no time, to add many things to it. But we made
this.

50
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:35,000
Bi lemsatên wekî dibe rîşê...
 
With the touches of, as they say, the brush...

51
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Yanî bes xuya dike ko ew karê di nav kurmanciya me da bû...
 
I mean it just shows that it was the work in our Kurdish
society...

52
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Cotyarên me, min didît di nava erdê me da, berê, bi
bêndergîr dajotin...
 
Our farmers, I used to see in our land, in the past, they
plowed with a thresher...

53
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Bi cota dewar dajotin... ha ev karê me ye.
 
They plowed with draft animals... here is our work.

54
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Û tiştê wilo jî, em pir jê hez dikin.
 
And such things too, we love very much.

55
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Her tiştkî kevin, çûçikatiya me tîne bîra me re, kalên me
tîne bîra me re...
 
Everything old, brings our childhood to our minds, brings
our elders to our minds...

56
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Û heta roha, em li bala xwe dinêrin... ev resmê min giştî
liser... liser vê gundê... kurmancan e.
 
And even today, we look at it... these paintings of mine are
all about... about this village... of the Kurds.

57
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Hemî gundên efrînê... wê kurmancan... e çûçikatiya me de, em
di xeyalên xwe da digerin li menatiqên efrînê, her tiştek me
dît...
 
All the villages of Afrin... of the Kurds... in our
childhood, we wander in our imaginations through the regions
of Afrin, everything we saw...

58
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Em tînin wêneyan, em tînin bîra min... ev te'me ji devê min
nare. Û heta ro ji, zane...
 
We bring them to paintings, we bring them to my mind... this
taste doesn't leave my mouth. And even today, you know...

59
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:26,000
Tiştên wisa wî wextî di malên me da pir bû, ez... ji xwe re
rûniştibûm min pê fikirîm...
 
Such things at that time were abundant in our homes, I... I
had sat down by myself and thought about it...

60
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Yanî gundê me berê çawa bû? Rêyên xwe çawa ne tenase...
 
I mean how was our village in the past? Its roads were
unpaved...

61
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Ew zagonên berê çûn neha ji wa... Kanî ez vegerim wê...
 
Those old traditions are gone now... Can I return to that...

62
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Min ev sûret, hewşên me ji wilo bûn. Gî sûr in naha? Gî sûr
in îro..
 
I made this painting, our courtyards were like that too.
They are all red now? They are all red today..

63
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Lê min nexwest, ev tîştên kevin min tu tîşt nû nekiriye.
 
But I didn't want it, these old things, I didn't make
anything new.

64
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:48,000
Bila ew ta'm di bîra me da bimîne inu berê em li vî yeki da
dijîn. Û pir tiştkî xweş e.
 
Let that taste stay in our memory that we used to live like
this. And it is a very nice thing.

65
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Heya nha ez dixwazim ku xaniyekê wilo da rûnim.
 
Even now I want to live in a house like that.

66
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Û her ez dikevimê ew tistên li xaniyek kevn ez dibînim ez
dûr diherim, se'atek du se'atan şikaran dipêm dipêm.
 
And whenever I encounter it, those things in an old house I
see, I go far, I spend an hour or two observing them.

67
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,000
Mamoste Mihemed em dixwazin gelek spas bikin.
 
Teacher Mihemed we want to thank you a lot.

68
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Wey ehlen we sehlen. Bi xêr hatin.
 
Oh welcome. Welcome.

69
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Pir, pir spas. Bi rastî weynên te pir xweş in û balkêş in.
 
Thank you very, very much. Truly your paintings are very
beautiful and interesting.

70
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Zef spas. Ser seran û ser çavan.
 
Thanks a lot. On my head and on my eyes.

71
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Gelek spas, em gelek kêfxweş in bi hatina te.
 
Thanks a lot, we are very happy to meet you.

72
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Û pir kêfxweş im bi we, û heke qisûra me hebû we efû bikin.
Wekî ehlen we sehlen.
 
And I am very happy with you, and if we had any flaws,
forgive us. Welcome.

73
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,000
Apê Zekeriya merheba çawa yî?
 
Uncle Zekeriya hello, how are you?

74
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:05,000
Hun bi xêr hatin ji we re. Û ji televîzyona Ronahî re.
 
Welcome to you. And to Ronahî television.

75
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:11,000
Û gavek pîroz e, hun werin gundê me. Hun bi xêr hatin
tekrar.
 
And it's a blessed step, that you come to our village.
Welcome again.

76
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,000
Spas ji te ra.
 
Thank you.

77
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,000
Apê Zekeriya navê Sînka ji kû hatiye?
 
Uncle Zekeriya, where does the name Sînka come from?

78
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:21,000
Welle, Sînka... pir riwayet hene, yanî pir av hene li ser...
 
Well, Sînka... there are many stories, I mean there are many
theories about it...

79
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:25,000
Hinek dibên li sîngî çiyê da ye... Hinek dibên navê teyrê
Sîngok e.
 
Some say it's on the chest (sîng) of the mountain... Some
say it's the name of the Sîngok bird.

80
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:29,000
Anîkê ev avê teyran.. sîngokek e, sînek e.
 
Meaning this bird... a woodpecker (sîngok), Sînek.

81
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Lekin ew... îhtîqadê min ew, ez bi yê bawer dikim...
 
But the... my belief is, the one I believe...

82
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:43,000
Ku Sînka Sîtka, ev beşek ji eşîreke kurdan e, eşîra Şikaka
ye.
 
That Sînka is Sîtka, this is a branch of a Kurdish tribe,
the Shikak tribe.

83
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:46,000
Em di defterê da gundekî ji gundê Şikaka ne.
 
On the registry, we are a village of the Shikak villages.

84
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Sê gundê Şikaka li dor Sînka heye. Sînka gundek e ji wa
gunda eşîra Şikaka ye.
 
There are three Shikak villages around Sînka. Sînka is one
of those villages of the Shikak tribe.

85
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:56,000
Ew girêdayî navçeya Şera ye hemî gundên vir?
 
Is it tied to the district of Shera, all the villages here?

86
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:02,000
Erê Şera. Yanî nêzîk e, heşt sed metir dûr e... navenda Şera
ji wê re heye nêzîk.
 
Yes Shera. I mean it's close, eight hundred meters away...
the center of Shera is close to it.

87
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Apê Zekeriya, gundê Sînka çend mal e?
 
Uncle Zekeriya, how many houses are in the village of Sînka?

88
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Welle dor pêncî... pênc malbat in. Dor pêncî malbat in.
 
Well around fifty... fifty families. Around fifty families.

89
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,000
Em nînin malbat, û çend mal in?
 
We don't mean families, but how many houses?

90
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:20,000
Mal, sê sed mal heye... sê sed mal heye. Lekin aîle...
hefsed heşt sed aîle heye.
 
Houses, there are three hundred houses... there are three
hundred houses. But families... there are seven hundred,
eight hundred families.

91
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Defter aîle mesela... ehwal medanî em dibêjin aîle. Heb e...
vî teqdîrî ye.
 
Family registries for example... civil records we say
family. There is... this is the estimate.

92
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:37,000
Û Sînka ji... ew şuhretî xwe di vê mentiqê da heye bi du
tişta.
 
And Sînka as well... has its fame in this region for two
things.

93
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Yek Sînka liser rêkê bazirganan e.
 
First, Sînka is on the merchant road.

94
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:47,000
Mentiqê me gî, îdarîyan ji wî ve girêdayî bûn bi Kilîs û
Ezazê.
 
All of our region, administratively they were connected to
Kilis and Azaz.

95
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Berî Cindirêsê.. yanî Cindirês.. naxêr Efrîn çêbibe?
 
Before Jindires.. I mean Jindires.. no, before Afrin was
established?

96
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:54,000
Efrîn tine bû wê çaxê, ew wextî...
 
Afrin didn't exist at that time, at that time...

97
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Hew bazirgan û rêwî û gîşt.. di Sînka ra diçûn...
 
Those merchants and travelers and everyone.. went through
Sînka...

98
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Bi rêkê diçûn... rêk di Sînka re dihat û du re derbas dibû.
 
They went through the road... the road came through Sînka
and then passed.

99
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Dera Ezaz, yek dera Kilîs. Û di Sînka ra rêkek heye dere
îstansyona Qitmê.
 
The Azaz road, the Kilis road. And through Sinka there's a
road going to the Qitme station.

100
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Ew jî di Sînka derbas dibe.
 
That also passes through Sinka.

101
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,000
Û tiştekî din li Sînka hebû...
 
And there was something else in Sinka...

102
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:14,000
Di orta gund da ode hebû.
 
In the middle of the village, there was a room.

103
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:21,000
Ode hebû, ji mêvana ra, ji rêwiya ra, ji bazirganiya ra,
rêkek ew der bû.
 
There was a room for guests, for travelers, for merchants,
that place was on the route.

104
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:26,000
Li vî gundî kî derbas dibû pirs dikirin ku, "Ew, em ku derê
herin?" Digotin, "Herin Sînka ode heye."
 
Whoever passed by this village would ask, "Where should we
go?" They would say, "Go to Sinka, there is a room."

105
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Û ev ode bi alîkariya gund bû û gundî gişt li dorê bû.
 
And this room was supported by the village and the villagers
were all around it.

106
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:36,000
Min dît... ez gîştime, bi alîkariya gund didan... û...
 
I saw... I reached the time, they gave it with the village's
help... and...

107
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:40,000
Yanî... ev nav û şuhreta Sînka ye.
 
I mean... this is the name and fame of Sinka.

108
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:44,000
Yanî ew ode ne yê kesekî bû yê gund giştî bû?
 
So that room didn't belong to one person, it belonged to the
whole village?

109
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:50,000
Erê, yê gund, bi alîkariya gund bû. Bi alîkariya gund bû.
 
Yes, it belonged to the village, with the village's help. It
was with the village's help.

110
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:57,000
Ev ode bi alîkariya gund bû, dereca selef... yanî di dereca
selef da.
 
This room was with the help of the village, to the degree of
predecessors... meaning in the degree of predecessors (in
older times).

111
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:03,000
Ê... û ew xeyrî... ode hat hilweşandin, heta niha nema.
 
Yeah... and besides that... the room was destroyed, it's no
longer there.

112
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Ode hîna heye yan?
 
Is the room still there or?

113
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Ode heye, heykelê gund e, heye, bes fitî xirab bûne, mal tê
de rûniştine.
 
The room is there, the structure is in the village, but the
arches are ruined, a family has settled in it.

114
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Yanî ne wezîfa xwe ye, ne wezîfa xwe ya kevn e.
 
I mean it doesn't serve its purpose, not its old purpose.

115
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,000
Ê di wî demî da mezinê we kî bû, ê gund?
 
And at that time, who was the elder of your village?

116
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Welle mezin... mezin hebûn...
 
Well, elders... there were elders...

117
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Mezin kalikê min... kalikê min hebû. Bapîrê gund ew hebû.
 
The elder was my grandfather... there was my grandfather.
There was the grandfather of the village.

118
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Kalikê min digotin Qere Elî... kalikê min... digotin Îbram
Axa, yê vira.
 
My grandfather they called Qere Ali... my grandfather...
they called Ibram Agha of here.

119
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:38,000
Ê... ev mezin bûn, û di Sînka da, yanî merivên mezin hebûn,
gişt li dorê bûn.
 
Yeah... these were elders, and in Sinka, I mean there were
great people, they were all around.

120
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:44,000
Yanî di Sînka da min dît... heyşt-deh meriv hebûn...
meriyên...
 
I mean in Sinka I saw... There were eight or ten men... men
of...

121
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,000
Rûspî.
 
Elders.

122
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:51,000
Rûspî, li dor gund bûn, ji bo wî gundî bûn.
 
Elders, they were around the village, they were for that
village.

123
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:54,000
Û gundê me, ev tiştê xwe din heye.
 
And our village, it has this other thing.

124
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:59,000
Gundê me tenê... nîvê Êzîdî ne, nîvê Misilman in.
 
Our village... half are Yazidis, half are Muslims.

125
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:07,000
Û ev... ev awa ji berê da heye. Û heta sekê da, di gund da
du bira hene, yek Êzîdî ye, yek Misilman e. Birakê hevdu ne.
 
And this... this state has existed since the past. And up to
now, there are two brothers in the village, one is Yazidi
and one is Muslim. They are brothers.

126
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Na gund berê destpêkê hemî Êzîdî bû, yan destpêkê da
Misilman û Êzîdî ne?
 
No, was the village entirely Yazidi in the beginning, or was
it Muslim and Yazidi from the start?

127
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:15,000
Na. Malbat hebûn, Êzîdî bûn.
 
No. There were families, they were Yazidis.

128
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:23,000
Nîvê îslam bûn, nîvê Êzîdî mane. Malbat hene îslam bûn.
Malbat hene Êzîdî bûn, kes jê îslam nebûye.
 
Half became Muslims, half remained Yazidis. There are
families that became Muslims. There are families that were
Yazidis, nobody from them became Muslim.

129
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Wisa mane. Yanî devî du nîv bû. Devî du nîv bû.
 
They remained like that. I mean it was two halves. It was
two halves.

130
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:32,000
Ev kesên ku Misilman bûne, ji kîjan salê da bûne Misilman?
 
These people who became Muslims, since what year did they
become Muslims?

131
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:40,000
Welle ji mêj ve... Û heta niha... yanî berî vê bi çend
sala... Êzîdî, yê xwe dixwaze Misilman dibe, divê.
 
Well, for a long time. And until now... I mean a few years
ago... a Yazidi who wants to become Muslim, becomes one.

132
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Yanî ne ew e, ne di fetreyek muayen da...
 
I mean it's not that, not in a specific period.

133
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,000
Ez di zikriyê min de berî vê bi çend sala...
 
I remember a few years ago...

134
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:50,000
Hinek hebûn Êzîdî bûn, go "em ê bibin Misilman", bûn
Misilman. Yanî ne ev... ew jî li ser ola xwe mane. Bê
keyfî...
 
There were some Yazidis who said "we will become Muslims"
and they became Muslims. I mean it's not that... They didn't
stay in their religion. Unwillingly...

135
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:58,000
Bi keyfa xwe bûn. Ne bi... ne bi zor bû, ne bi tişt bû, na.
 
It was of their own will. Not by... it wasn't by force, or
by anything else, no.

136
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:07,000
Pirsek din... Naha di Çiyayê Kurmênc da gelek... geliyê
kuştiya... ew nav ji ku hatiye?
 
Another question... Now in Kurd Dagh, there are many... the
valley of the killed... where does this name come from?

137
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Çima dibêjin geliyê kuştiya?
 
Why do they call it the valley of the killed?

138
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Geliyê kuştiya... ev bi aliyê... bi aliyê Qitmê da ye.
 
The valley of the killed... that is in the direction of...
in the direction of Qitme.

139
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,000
Arleqê Qitmê û Sînka da ye.
 
It's between Qitme and Sinka.

140
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Ê... em nizanin... yanî kes nizane vê hadîsê bi zept çiye.
Bes ji navê gund ra...
 
Yeah... we don't know... I mean nobody knows what this
incident exactly is. But from the village's name...

141
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Meriv zane ku kuştin... kuştin di wî derî dîtine.
 
One knows that a killing... killings were seen there.

142
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:36,000
Naha pirsek din heye, te got pazdeh malbat hene? Te karî
navî van malbatan yek bi yek ji me re xuyan bikî?
 
Now there is another question, you said there are fifteen
families? Could you point out the names of these families
one by one for us?

143
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Eşker dikim. Mala Îsa...
 
I will reveal them. Isa family...

144
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Malek kevn e di gund da.
 
It's an old family in the village.

145
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,000
Çawîşa...
 
Çawîş family...

146
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Cafera...
 
Cafer family...

147
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Çurûkzada...
 
Çurûkzad family...

148
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,000
Mala Cerah...
 
Cerah family...

149
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,000
Mala Mûsê Begê...
 
Mûsê Beg family...

150
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:53,000
Mala Hemê û Hemkerê...
 
Hemê and Hemker family...

151
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,000
Mala Hemûşê...
 
Hemûş family...

152
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,000
Xeleb Dalo...
 
Xeleb Dalo...

153
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,000
Hûr Betalo...
 
Hûr Betalo...

154
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,000
Bekir Endiya...
 
Bekir Endiya...

155
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Şêx û Bekriya... evna Êzîdî ne.
 
Şêx and Bekri family... these are Yazidis.

156
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,000
Mala Sorik...
 
Sorik family...

157
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,000
El Çepera...
 
El Çeper family...

158
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,000
Mala Xawêr...
 
Xawêr family...

159
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,000
Mala Heswiyê Qitmê.
 
Heswiyê Qitmê family.

160
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Evna malbatên Sînka ne.
 
These are the families of Sinka.

161
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Pazdeh malbat ne?
 
Fifteen families, right?

162
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:20,000
Pazdeh malbat e... Mala Îsa... Êzîdî bûn, nîvê îslam in...
noka nîvê Êzîdî mane.
 
Fifteen families... Isa family... were Yazidi, half are
Muslim... now half remained Yazidi.

163
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,000
Malên we ava be, saetên we xweş.
 
Bless your home, have a good time.

164
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Avahiya we jî xweş, û serkeftin be.
 
Bless your lives too. And wishing you success.

165
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Gundê Sînka, yek ji kevintirîn navçeya Şera ye. Û li milê
rojhilatî wê ye.
 
Sinka village, one of the oldest in the Shera district. And
it is on its eastern side.

166
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:38,000
Hejmara şêniyên gund 3440 kes in.
 
The population of the village is 3440 people.

167
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Û ji 300 malî pêk tê.
 
And it consists of 300 houses.

168
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:44,000
Nîvê xelkê vî gundî bawermendên ola Êzdatî ne.
 
Half of the people in this village are believers of the
Yazidi religion.

169
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:47,000
Û nîviyê din jî Misilman in.
 
And the other half are Muslims.

170
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Lê ev nîviyê Misilman jî... ne pir ji mêj ve derbasî ola
Misilmantiya bûne.
 
But this Muslim half... it hasn't been long since they
converted to Islam.

171
00:14:52,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Dewleta Baasê, siyaseta qirkirina ola Êzîdî, bi awayekî şerê
sar... berdewam kir.
 
The Ba'athist state continued the policy of eradicating the
Yazidi religion through a kind of cold war.

172
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:06,000
Lewma jî... hejmarek mezin ji gel... dev ji ola bav û kalên
xwe berdan...
 
Therefore... a large number of people... abandoned the
religion of their ancestors...

173
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Ji bo ku, bi aramî bijîn.
 
In order to live in peace.

174
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Wateya gotina Sînka, ji navê êla Sînka ya şikakî hatiye
dariştin.
 
The meaning of the word Sinka is derived from the name of
the Sinka tribe of the Shikaki.

175
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:33,000
Lê hinek çavkaniyên gund jî dibêjin, ku gotina Sînka ji
singê çiyê hatiye lêkirin.
 
But some village sources also say, that the word Sinka was
built from the chest of the mountain.

176
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:36,000
Lê wateya yekemîn rasttir e.
 
But the first meaning is more correct.

177
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:56,000
Ji ber ku êla Sînka pir fireh û mezin bûbû, û çûne herdu
gundên Baflûn û Qestel Cindo da bi cîh bûne.
 
Because the Sinka tribe had become very broad and large, and
they went and settled in the two villages of Baflun and
Qestel Jindo.

178
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:05,000
Lê Leyla, lê Leylan e...
 
Oh Leyla, oh Leyla...

179
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Li çol û baniyan e...
 
In the plains and highlands...

180
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:12,000
Qîza Heyder Axan e...
 
The daughter of Heyder Agha...

181
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Li ber kerî û berxan e...
 
Tending to the flocks and lambs...

182
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Bavkê bi dengekî bang kir, go Leyla meyarim were viran e...
 
The father called out, saying Leyla, my dear, come here...

183
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:24,000
Ê yarim go biqetîne benê stûyê kûçan e...
 
My dear said cut the rope around the dogs' necks...

184
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Mala bar kir çûne zozan e... qîza mamê, şûna gîyan e...
 
The family packed up and went to the summer pastures...
cousin, place of souls...

185
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Ê la bavo, go na qetînim benê stûyê kûçan e...
 
Oh father, she said I won't cut the rope around the dogs'
necks...

186
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:38,000
Darnek xwarim çiyayê Bîlan e, leylan e...
 
I ate a bad fruit at Mount Bilan, oh Leyla...

187
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:44,000
Bîlan e...
 
It is Bilan...

188
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:53,000
Şêniyên gundê Sînka, ji bo peydakirina debara xwe dispêrin
ser çandiniya darên zeytûn... mişmiş... hinar... sêv... û
mêweyan.
 
The residents of Sinka village rely on cultivating olive...
apricot... pomegranate... apple... and fruit trees to make a
living.

189
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:59,000
Jinên gundê Sînka, erzaq an mûnetê salê ji werzê havînê da
didin hev.
 
The women of Sinka village gather the provisions or yearly
supplies from the summer season.

190
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Her wek... penêr, meqdûs, reçela mişmiş...
 
Such as... cheese, makdous, apricot jam...

191
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:10,000
Gêlaz, hejîr û gundiran di werzê çileyê da dixwin.
 
Cherries, figs, and squash, they eat them in the winter
season.

192
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:14,000
Ji ber ku di dema berê da sarinc û ferezê jî nînbûn...
 
Because in the old days there were no refrigerators or
freezers...

193
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,000
Dayîk û kebaniyên malan, keskayî hişk dikirin.
 
Mothers and housewives used to dry greens.

194
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:23,000
Her wek bacanên sor û reş, bamye, îsotên sor...
 
Like red and black tomatoes (eggplants), okra, red
peppers...

195
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Gundir û lûpik... di werzê zivistanê da dikirin xwarin.
 
Squash and beans... they would cook them in the winter
season.

196
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Her wiha ji nav ava baranan, şerab û qorix, û dimsê hinaran
jî bi kar tanîn.
 
Furthermore, from the rain and water, they also used wine,
grape juice, and pomegranate molasses.

197
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja.
 
Yes, our dear viewers.

198
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:08,000
Di gundê Sînka da, îro em digerin. Naha jî em derbasî ser
ziyareta Şêx Reman bûn.
 
Today we are touring Sinka village. Now we have arrived at
the shrine of Sheikh Reman.

199
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Dayikek ji me re hatin vir, behsa vê ziyaretê kirin.
 
A mother came to us here, and talked about this shrine.

200
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:15,000
Me go em derbas bin, em çîroka ziyaretê nas bikin. Merheba
jin xaltî.
 
We said let's go in and get to know the story of the shrine.
Hello, auntie.

201
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:19,000
Ehlen û sehlen. Ser serê me, ser çavê me hûn hatin.
 
Welcome. You've come upon our heads, upon our eyes.

202
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:23,000
Qedem xêr, hûn ser serê me... bi xêr û silamet hatin cem me.
Hûn bûn mêvanê me.
 
Auspicious footsteps, you upon our heads... welcome in peace
and safety to us. You've become our guests.

203
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,000
Pir spas, xaltî can.
 
Thank you so much, dear auntie.

204
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,000
Dayê me we behsa ziyaretekê kir, we go ziyaret e... dema
zarok nameşin...
 
Mother, you mentioned a shrine, you said the shrine... for
when children don't walk...

205
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Bi taybet zarok... em tînin vira û bi destên wî digirin û
zarok dimeşe.
 
Especially children... we bring them here, take them by the
hand and the child walks.

206
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Me jî, ji lewma.. te dît... zinar dît...
 
We also, that's why we saw you, we saw the rock...

207
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,000
Hûn çawa dikin yanî?
 
How do you do it, I mean?

208
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Em berê... vira gişt... yanî qarac bû, mal tune bûn.
 
We used to... here it was all... I mean it was bushes, there
were no houses.

209
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Û taht mezin bûn yanî fireh bû.
 
And the rocks were big, I mean it was wide.

210
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:54,000
Û dianîn... qeçikî, çûçikî yanî du salî, sê salî, heta çar
salî nameşî, dextor tune bûn.
 
And they would bring... a boy, a little one, I mean two
years old, three years old, up to four years old who wasn't
walking, there were no doctors.

211
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Qinaeta xwe... piranî dextora ne dikirin, qinaeta xwe bi
ziyaretan di- dikirin.
 
Their belief... mostly they wouldn't take them to doctors,
they put their faith in the shrines.

212
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:05,000
Û dihatin... destê wî qeçikî digirtin... eva destan digirtin
an... li dorê ra digerandin, digerandin...
 
And they would come... hold the hand of that little child...
take these hands... and walk them around it, walk them...

213
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,000
Û dîtina xwa jî, Şêx Reman e...
 
And in their belief, this is Sheikh Reman...

214
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Û dihatin yanî wî qeçikî, û xwarê gund jî dibirin... di
kûçên gund didan.
 
And they would come, I mean that child, and take them down
to the village... they would let them in the village alleys.

215
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Yanî qerarê mehekî, bîst roj, ev qeçiko radibû, dimeşî.
 
I mean in about a month, twenty days, this child would get
up and walk.

216
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:19,000
Ê dayê li vir ziyaret tune, yanî tenê zinar e?
 
But mother, there is no shrine here, I mean it's just a
rock?

217
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,000
Erê, zinar e. Ziyaret tenê...
 
Yes, it's a rock. Just the shrine...

218
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:29,000
Tirbe li vir tune, goristan tune... De de em çawa... dibêjin
dîtin gund da wekî civan dibêjin Şêx Xerîb heye, ew ziyaret
e...
 
There is no tomb here, no graveyard... Then how... they say
in the village like the youth say there is Sheikh Xerib,
that's a shrine...

219
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:32,000
Qubbe ji heye... vir goristan in...
 
It also has a dome... here are graveyards...

220
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:37,000
Li vir jî me tişt nedît, tenê zinar e. We hûn bi baweriya
xwe li vir dikin, hûn tên li dor vir digerin.
 
Here we didn't see anything, it's just a rock. But you put
your faith in it, you come and walk around here.

221
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:44,000
Erê qinaeta xwe pê dikirin, li dorê ra digerandin, berê da
tirb tune bûn, bes hone fere bû, taht hone wê derê gişt fere
bû.
 
Yes, they put their faith in it, they would walk around it,
there were no tombs before, but it was wide like this, the
rock here was wide everywhere.

222
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:49,000
Çunkî mal der tişt tune bû, vêra digotin Serî Dêr. Vira...
yanî diyar e Serî Dêr e.
 
Because there were no houses or anything outside, they
called this Seri Der. Here... I mean it's known as Seri Der.

223
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:55,000
Û dihatin vê derê... û em çûçik bûn... em qeçik bûn... yanî
e mezin dihatin... em vê ra dihatin.
 
And they would come here... and we were little... we were
kids... I mean the elders would come... we would come with
them.

224
00:19:55,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Û hevîrê xwe jî li ber dikirin, û şekir di nav dikirin, û
pare jî dikirin... a eva ye...
 
And they would also knead their dough by it, and they would
put sugar in it, and share it... ah this is it...

225
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:05,000
Û mane ev qîçkoyî li ber xanê da dimeşî.
 
And so this little child was walking in front of the house.

226
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,000
Ey heyat çend mehî, çend salî ye hezar û yek...
 
Well life, how many months, how many years is a thousand and
one...

227
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:13,000
Yanî qerarê meşê, meselan e qîçikê heye yek salî û şûn da
eke dimeşe.
 
I mean the rule of walking, for example this child here,
after a year she will walk.

228
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:16,000
Ê dema wextê meşê dibe bimeşin bînine der a?
 
And when it is time to walk, if they don't walk, you bring
them out?

229
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Erê, yek salî û şûn da nameşî, yanî he qîçik ku bi xwe
nameşî.
 
Yes, if they don't walk after a year, I mean if this child
doesn't walk by herself.

230
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:24,000
Salek salnîvek du sal emrê xwe, he qîçik gerek bimeşe û
nameşe.
 
A year, a year and a half, two years of age, this child
needs to walk but doesn't walk.

231
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Tên, dorî vî darî, dorî hanê ro digerînin, û he quçkî li ber
xaneya dimeşin. Dimeşî.
 
They come, take them around this tree, around that place,
and this child walks in front of the house. Walks.

232
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Ê de zarokê gund da nameşî hanîne bîra?
 
And when the village child wouldn't walk, did they bring
them to mind?

233
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:37,000
